What a glorious morning, an entirely empty beach, didn't see a single person until mid afternoon. Blue sky, tranquil, not much of a swell, but the perfect conditions to immerse ourselves in calmness, simplicity and peace.
There seems to be a myth that we need drama for impressive landscape photography, dynamic light, pointy mountains and sunsets. 
Today the landscape perfectly reflected my mood; openness, tranquility and gratitude. Just to be there was such a great pleasure.
For this image I used my Kase Filters UK 6 stop ND and a reverse 3 stop grad. The colour rendition of the scene was just perfect and I've barely had to do any processing at all. #kasefiltersuk #kasefilters #scotlandshots #expressivephotography #nikon #rps

Many of my fellow photographers are looking back on the year and the photographs they have made. Instead, I want to look back and remember the times I have had in the field, but more so the people I got do do that with. Experiencing, sharing joy, foul weather, laughter, a whisky or two, a look of mutual appreciation for being there, together. Life can be cruel, so many people suffer and die needlessly, or in a moment of their own despair. 
At this time of year, as we look back, looking forward and sharing time with loved ones, I want to extend my thanks, not just as an artist, but as a man who is grateful for all I have in the world, but get the greatest sense of achievement from what I can do to help others.

Thank you to everyone who has supported Expressive Photography this year. We look forward to moving our work to greater heights in 2023.

Big thaw on now on the west of Scotland, really rather mild today, but shocked to here Bilbao had +25C on New Year’s Day. That’s just mad and with water shortages already reported there it sounds like a very bleak summer ahead.
As landscape photographers, we tend to show the beauty of the world, or a distillation sanitised and sparkling. I see a future where we record more honestly the state of the landscape. 
Having said that, there is still a place for pure aesthetics. Be they beautiful or challenging. 
Art is the expression of our perspectives.
Or is it just a tree in the snow?

Super busy day; 3 mentorships, a bunch of admin, a 10 km run and lots of planning for the upcoming Spain workshops that start on the 16th. For the past few years I have been moving away from shooting scenes, landscapes in a broader sense, and concentrating on small part so landscapes. I enjoy confluences, juxtapositions, counterparts and the relationships these form.

Yes, this is a scene of rocks and water in a literal sense, but to me, it also has an architectural core of geometric shapes, built upon colours, and tones and textures.

A rich tapestry of different parts, that I feel holds together in a very pleasing way.

Maybe when I get to Spain and we're looking across familiar coastal landscapes I will see and feel differently, but for now, I feel contained within a concept! #kasefiltersuk #fstopgear #expressivephotography

Why show the source when you can show the effect? I see so many images of star bursts and wide landscapes, and they are beautiful and impressive, but they also take a lot of technique in the field and in front of the computer. By pointing the camera in the opposite direction we can photograph the beautiful warm light reflecting off mountains, or cliffs. These powerful reflections are so beautiful and carry the same uplifting vibe as any sunrise image. This one was taken on the north coast of Spain in January while I was running a couple of workshops with my good buddy @adamgibbsphoto . When I started back with photography in 2002 I was desperately in need of something to take me out of myself, reconnect with nature and find a sanctuary far from the stress of a high end corporate career. I found it in the wild places of Asia, Nepal, Tibet and the Himalaya. But I started with birds, my first love, and my childhood passion that shaped me as a person. The intricate beauty of an Anna’s Hummingbird, or the incongruous behaviours of a Long-billed Dowitcher, staring through the lens created a conduit for self-expression and discovery of nature and myself. As the years progressed and I developed the concepts of expressive photography, the 5 triggers of engagement, and now, exploring with my friends on the EP forum, the attributes of behaviours and how they are mirrored in nature, we can develop a new language, an expressive one, articulation of nuances deep and meaningful. Yes, these are photographs of a mountains, or some west coast USA birds, but to me they express my passion for being in a place and building relationships with it and it’s inhabitants. Photography is the gift that keeps on giving. Why do you do it? #kasefilters_uk #kasefiltersglobal #fstopgear #expressivephotography

I get asked all the time about Expressive Photography. What is it, do I need to talk about my feelings and emotions, is it just weird abstracts and small scenes? Well, no, none of the above. All experiences that we have in nature (or even in urban areas, or parks) can result in expressive photography. I’m this image, I remember well the Great White Egret shining against the dark water background. These birds are so elegant, perfect hunters and beautiful to look at. I used to spend hours crouched beside their pool, waiting for the moment to press the shutter, often at the moment if striking for a fish. So, is this image expressive? If so what is it expressing? I know the answers, but I’d be interested in your feedback. #kasefiltersglobal #kasefilters_uk #fstopgear #expressivephotography #birdphotography

50km mountain bike ride before breakfast and what a beautiful morning. Calm and clear after a few very wet and windy days. A couple of otters in the Loch and a giant red deer stag that nearly knocked me off my bike as it bolted out of the woods! A great start to the day.

As you know we are just back from Iceland and it is exciting for me to see the others from the trip sharing their images. All so different, all so unique and all so inspiring. Our itinerary made for some long drives, from Keflavik, up to Snaefellsness, across an empty quarter to the western fjords and then the real long haul across the north to Myvatn (darned bugs!) and then back to the airport. Many of our opportunities on the driving days were brief, little moments when nature just threw us some amazing light and we slammed to a haul, pilled out the van and shot vistas hand held.
This was on the drive up towards the western fjords across a somewhat desolate stretch of dirt road, with few cars and less services.
Just a little moment of engagement that I can relive through processing this image. #kasefiltersglobal #kasefilters_uk #expressivephotography #zoegraphy #iceland

Nature and landscape photography is a huge gift. If we have the time, money, health  and opportunity to get out into the landscape, we are rich indeed. For some though that is not enough; they feel compelled to trample fragile vegetation, break branches, or stand on fragile rock formations destroying them forever. For what? To get a shot that makes other people think they are something special, advocates for the natural world, at one with their environment. On Sunday I post a video where I speak my mind and the truth; if you’re a photographer who destroys nature to get a shot then you’re a huge problem and no ambassador for our art. #expressivephotography #creativity #naturefirst #ethics #moralcompass #zoegraphy #kasefiltersglobal #kasefilters_uk

It has been said that photography is a marriage of art and craft, but does that also describe creativity? This is the first blended multiple exposure I think I have produced since perhaps 2016. From 2017 when I went into the Gobi desert and pretty much changed my life and myself, I have not had the desire, and have lost some of the skills I once had. I had to really think about this image to make it; remembering how to do things, which masks to choose, how to apply them and various other little tricks I used to do without thought. However, I like the image, I enjoyed the time close to the waves, waiting for the one that would get over the top of my boots and make my feet wet! I have found passion again. #kasefiltersglobal #kasefilters_uk #expressivephotography #workshops #blend #multipleexposures #seascapephotography
